title: Kim Kardashian, Anna Wintour, Kylie Jenner and Tyga sit on the front row at Kanye West's Yeezy Season 5 show
text:
Kim Kardashian, Anna Wintour, Kylie Jenner and Tyga sit on the front row at Kanye West's Yeezy Season 5 show The rapper's new line features more neutral colours, camo prints, velvet hooded sweaters and fur jackets Share Get daily updates directly to your inbox + Subscribe Thank you for subscribing! Could not subscribe, try again later Invalid Email 
Kanye West debuted his latest collection, Yeezy Season 5, during New York Fashion Week on Wednesday. 
The rapper invited all his A List pals, with the likes of Anna Wintour and Carine Roitfeld sat alongside Kardashian-Jenner family members. 
Tyga and Kylie sat next to each other, while Kim was positioned next to the Vogue head honcho. 
After his extravaganza at Madison Square Garden last year, this year's show - held at Pier 59 Studios - was a lot more laid back. Kim Kardashian, Anna Wintour (Photo: Splash News) Kim Kardashian watches the Yeezy 5 show with Kylie Jenner and many more celebs (Photo: Splash News) 
The upcoming collection features brighter colours than previous lines and also camo prints, velvet hooded sweaters and fur jackets. 
Other guests at the show included Hailey Baldwin, Teyana Taylor and La La Anthony. 
But it was Kim who really stole the show in a tight-fitting maroon outfit that went a tad sheer under the glare of the paparazzi cameras. 
The reality babe's nipples were on clear display in the clinging, see-through look. Hailey Baldwin, La La Anthony (Photo: Splash News) Hailey Baldwin and Teanna Taylor (Photo: Splash News) Kim Kardashian watches the Yeezy 5 show with Kylie Jenner and many more celebs (Photo: Splash News) 
Kim's mum Kris Jenner said last week that Kanye missed the Grammy Awards so he could focus on building his fashion empire and prepare for Wednesday's show. 
Kris said on the red carpet: "The truth is he's got a big fashion show in New York because it's New York Fashion Week. And my entire family is back there. ... Some of the kids are on their way tomorrow. He's got a lot of work to do. We wish he could be here!" Video Loading Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now
